==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neaped
<hw>Neaped</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Left
aground on the height of a spring tide, so that it will not float till
the next spring tide; -- called also
<altname>beneaped</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neapolitan</ent>⟦br⟧
